<TITLE> Zia, Rakib, Reefat in winning streak in Mayors Cup Chess </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 13 (bdnews24.com) -Three Bangladeshi Grand Masters along with 11 players shared lead in the Mayors Cup First International Open Chess Tournament at the end of the fourth round games Tuesday in the Indian city of Mumbai. GM Ziaur Rahman, GM Abdullah Al Rakib and GM Reefat Bin Sattar secured maximum four points from as many games. In the day's games, Zia beat Indian Shashikant Kutwal, Rakib beat Indian International Master Sudhakar Babu and Reefat beat Indian IM DP Singh. Some 288 players including 14 grandmasters and 24 International Masters from different countries are participating in the event. 
